{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "01", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "01", "M": "53", "S": "12"}}, "news": [{"title": "RR Kabel's net profit rises 57.96% in FY26", "para": "RR Kabel's net profit surged by over 57 percent, reaching \u20b9492.21 crore for the fiscal year 2025-26. Total income also saw a substantial increase of 27.50 percent, amounting to \u20b99,778.78 crore. The Wires & Cables business was a major contributor to this success.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/rr-kabels-net-profit-rises-57-96-in-fy26/130631142?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-93986/130631142.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Kajaria Ceramics' net profit rises 62.32% in FY26; approves \u20b9297 crore share buyback", "para": "Kajaria Ceramics announced a significant 62.32 percent jump in net profit for FY26, reaching \u20b9487 crore. Total income also saw a rise. The company is investing \u20b9210 crore to expand its manufacturing capacity in Andhra Pradesh. Additionally, a share buyback of up to \u20b9296.7 crore has been approved. A final dividend of \u20b96 per share is recommended.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/kajaria-ceramics-net-profit-rises-62-32-in-fy26-approves-297-crore-share-buyback/130630636?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-57832/130630636.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Bombay HC steps into Decathlon-Godrej clash over prime Chembur lease", "para": "The Bombay High Court has placed prime Chembur commercial space under judicial protection amid a lease dispute. The court questioned if Decathlon's lease was terminated for a more lucrative deal with Titan, appointing a Receiver to take possession. This move signals a significant intervention in commercial fairness.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bombay-hc-steps-into-decathlon-godrej-clash-over-prime-chembur-lease/130630728?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-105738/130630728.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Allahabad HC refuses to entertain plea on Sahara Shahar land lease", "para": "The Allahabad High Court has rejected a plea from Sahara India Commercial Corporation Limited, which aimed to overturn the Lucknow Municipal Corporation's decision to revoke the land lease for the Sahara Shahar complex. The court indicated that it is unable to intervene at this time due to pending matters in the Supreme Court.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/allahabad-hc-refuses-to-entertain-plea-on-sahara-shahar-land-lease/130628664?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-92724/130628664.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Homebuilder Persimmon sees energy price-led cost inflation, holds 2026 delivery target", "para": "Persimmon faces rising costs from energy prices extending into next year.  However, the company maintains its home delivery forecast.  Robust sales growth is reported for the initial months of 2026.  In-house production offers resilience against material cost hikes.  Early signs of supply chain inflation are noted for late 2026 and 2027.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/homebuilder-persimmon-sees-energy-price-led-cost-inflation-holds-2026-delivery-target/130628003?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-408366/130628003.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "international"}, {"title": "Smartworks Coworking Spaces posts net profit of \u20b910.52 crore in FY26", "para": "Smartworks Coworking Spaces achieved a net profit of \u20b910.52 crore and total income of \u20b91,849.90 crore in FY26. The company expanded its operational portfolio to over 10 million sq ft.  In Q4 FY26, total income was \u20b9532.70 crore with a profit after tax of \u20b916.62 crore.  The company ended FY26 with net cash and reduced its gross debt significantly.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/smartworks-coworking-spaces-posts-net-profit-of-10-52-crore-in-fy26/130627700?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-38236/130627700.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Lift safety checks lag in Pune, Mumbai divisions as recent mishaps in Nashik sound alarm bells", "para": "Lift safety inspections are alarmingly low in Pune and parts of Mumbai, with only 25.62% compliance in Pune city. Recent fatal incidents in Nashik highlight the risks of missed mandatory annual checks. Officials cite staff shortages and increasing workloads as key challenges, despite state-level announcements of new inspector posts and improved procedures.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/urgent-need-for-lift-safety-inspections-in-pune-and-mumbai-amid-rising-accidents/130627099?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-87170/130627099.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Dehradun administration cancels registration of 17 illegal homestays", "para": "Dehradun district administration has cancelled registrations of 17 homestays in Sahaspur and Raipur as part of 'Operation Safai' due to violations. Inspections revealed issues like lack of proper facilities, fire safety lapses, and unauthorized commercial use. This action aims to ensure homestays adhere to regulations and promote local culture.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/hospitality/dehradun-cancels-registration-of-17-illegal-homestays-facing-violations/130627243?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26282/130627243.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "hospitality"}, {"title": "Accenture leases over six lakh sq ft in Pune, plans GCC in long-term \u20b9325 crore deal", "para": "Accenture has secured a significant office space of over 600,000 sq ft in Pune. This new facility will house a global capability centre. The occupation will occur in two phases, concluding by June. This expansion is part of a larger strategy to enhance operational efficiency and consolidate teams.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/accenture-secures-major-office-lease-in-pune-for-global-capability-centre/130622046?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-51323/130622046.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Haryana: DTCP orders statewide audit of infrastructure, funds", "para": "The Department of Town and Country Planning is collecting data on infrastructure, encroachments, and funds. This follows a High Court order concerning the stilt-plus-four-floor policy. Urban agencies must submit detailed reports soon. The court is assessing if infrastructure can support increased density. Approvals for S+4 floors are currently halted. This exercise will inform future policy decisions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/haryana-dtcp-launches-statewide-audit-on-infrastructure-and-funds-following-high-court-order/130621792?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-121440/130621792.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Telangana government signs agreement with L&T for acquisition of 100% equity shares of LTMRHL", "para": "The Telangana government has successfully acquired complete ownership of Hyderabad Metro Rail Phase I. They inked a Share Purchase Agreement with L&T, securing 100 percent equity shares in a deal worth Rs 1,461.47 crores.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/telangana-government-signs-agreement-with-lt-for-acquisition-of-100-equity-shares-of-ltmrhl/130621354?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-71044/130621354.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Kone strikes $34 billion deal to buy TK Elevator and create world's largest lift maker", "para": "Finnish lift maker Kone is set to acquire German rival TK Elevator for 29.4 billion euros. This deal will create the world's largest lift maker. Kone aims to expand its presence in the Americas. The merger is expected to yield significant cost savings. Regulatory approvals are anticipated to take 12 to 18 months.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/kone-strikes-34-billion-deal-to-buy-tk-elevator-and-create-worlds-largest-lift-maker/130621290?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-94792/130621290.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "international"}, {"title": "Brigade Group & Bain Capital to jointly develop two million sq ft project in Bengaluru", "para": "Brigade Group and Bain Capital are joining forces for a major development in Whitefield, Bengaluru. This 50:50 joint venture will invest approximately \u20b92,200 crore. The project will span 11 acres, featuring two million sq ft of grade-A office space and a five-star hotel. It recently acquired land in Osman Nagar, Hyderabad for a residential project.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/brigade-group-bain-capital-to-jointly-develop-two-million-sq-ft-project-in-bengaluru/130610727?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-238174/130610727.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Mindspace Business Parks REIT's net operating income up 29.2% in FY26", "para": "Mindspace REIT announces 29.2 percent growth in net operating income for the financial year 2025-26. The company's board has approved raising funds up to \u20b915,700 crore. A distribution of \u20b96.64 per unit has been declared for the quarter ending March 31, 2026.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/mindspace-business-parks-reits-net-operating-income-up-29-2-in-fy26/130608517?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-93986/130608517.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Ramky Estates takes over stalled Skylark projects in Bengaluru, secures \u20b9600 crore SWAMIH funding", "para": "Ramky Estates has taken over stalled residential projects spanning 4.3 million sq ft in Bengaluru from Skylark Builders, with \u20b9600 crore funding from the SWAMIH Fund to support completion. The projects have an estimated revenue potential of \u20b92,000 crore.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ramky-estates-revives-skylark-projects-in-bengaluru-with-600-crore-swamih-fund/130621711?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-105736/130621711.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "County Group acquires two stalled housing projects in Gurugram", "para": "County Group has acquired two stalled housing projects in Gurgaon, offering relief to nearly 400 homebuyers. The acquisitions provide the developer with 2.6 million sq ft of saleable area and an estimated revenue potential of Rs 4,000 crore. This move aims to revive projects that have been delayed for over a decade.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/county-group-revives-housing-projects-in-gurugram-securing-homes-for-400-buyers/130621494?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22988/130621494.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}